snippet.textDisplay:
Pausing video to get my guesses down for the 2 most influential games of the decade:
PUBG and League of Legends.
Pubg may not have been the first Battle Royale but it was Pubg's massive success that basically created the Battle Royale Genre and gave birth to the clones that came after it (notably Fortnite). League of Legends for the same reasons as Pubg (but with the MOBA explosion (and to a lesser extent, auto-chess)).
My honourable mentions:
-Dark Souls - the soulslike genre (I feel) is a strong but recent trend and this is a decade-long retrospective.
-Minecraft's influence was huge; giving starts to countless Youtube channels (plus Merch, spin-offs ect) but it didn't inspire clones and thus create a genre. It was huge, sure but singular.
Just my 2 cents before I keep watching. :)
